# ============================================================================
# Fortemi Workstation — LLM Backend Configuration
# ============================================================================
#
# Copy this file to `.env.workstation` and uncomment ONE provider block.
# The compose file will pick it up automatically the next time you run
# `./workstation up`.
#
#   cp .env.workstation.example .env.workstation
#   $EDITOR .env.workstation              # uncomment one block
#   ./workstation up
#
# Or use the wizard:
#
#   ./workstation configure-llm
#
# .env.workstation is gitignored — your API keys never get committed.
#
# Five options below. Pick the one that matches what you have:
#
#   1. ollama-local       Docker-managed Ollama (default — no action needed)
#   2. vllm-local         vLLM running on your host machine
#   3. openai-cloud       Real OpenAI API (paid, requires API key)
#   4. openrouter         OpenRouter cloud router (paid, requires API key)
#   5. llamacpp-local     llama.cpp server running on your host machine
#
# ============================================================================


# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Option 1 — Ollama (Docker container, default)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This is the default behavior. You do NOT need to set anything for this
# option — the compose file's built-in env vars already point at the
# containerized Ollama. If you've created .env.workstation with this block
# uncommented, it just reaffirms the defaults explicitly.
#
# MATRIC_INFERENCE_DEFAULT=ollama
# OLLAMA_BASE=http://ollama:11434
# OLLAMA_GEN_MODEL=qwen3.5:9b
# OLLAMA_EMBED_MODEL=nomic-embed-text


# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Option 2 — vLLM running on the host machine
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# You started vLLM yourself with something like:
#
#   vllm serve meta-llama/Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct --port 8000
#
# vLLM exposes an OpenAI-compatible API, so we route it through the
# `openai` provider with a custom base URL.
#
# IMPORTANT — networking from inside the Docker container:
#   - Linux:    use http://host.docker.internal:8000  (the compose file
#               wires host-gateway → host.docker.internal for you)
#   - macOS:    use http://host.docker.internal:8000  (works natively)
#   - Windows:  use http://host.docker.internal:8000  (WSL2 + Docker Desktop)
#
# vLLM does NOT serve embeddings. Pair with containerized Ollama for the
# embedding side (MATRIC_EMBEDDING_PROVIDER=ollama below).
#
# MATRIC_INFERENCE_DEFAULT=openai
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=http://host.docker.internal:8000/v1
# OPENAI_API_KEY=not-needed-but-required-by-client
# OPENAI_GEN_MODEL=meta-llama/Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct
# MATRIC_EMBEDDING_PROVIDER=ollama
# OLLAMA_BASE=http://ollama:11434
# OLLAMA_EMBED_MODEL=nomic-embed-text


# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Option 3 — OpenAI (real, paid)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Uses api.openai.com. You need an API key from
# https://platform.openai.com/api-keys.
#
# Embeddings are billed the same as generation — be aware of cost if you
# import a large support archive. To keep embeddings free and local, set
# MATRIC_EMBEDDING_PROVIDER=ollama and the embeddings will route through
# the containerized Ollama instead.
#
# MATRIC_INFERENCE_DEFAULT=openai
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...replace-with-your-key...
# OPENAI_GEN_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini
# OPENAI_EMBED_MODEL=text-embedding-3-small
# # Optional — keep embeddings local and free:
# # MATRIC_EMBEDDING_PROVIDER=ollama
# # OLLAMA_BASE=http://ollama:11434
# # OLLAMA_EMBED_MODEL=nomic-embed-text


# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Option 4 — OpenRouter (cloud multi-provider router)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OpenRouter routes to Anthropic, OpenAI, Google, and many others through
# a single OpenAI-compatible API. Get a key at https://openrouter.ai/keys.
#
# OpenRouter does NOT serve embeddings — you MUST pair with Ollama (or
# OpenAI/llama.cpp) for embeddings via MATRIC_EMBEDDING_PROVIDER.
#
# MATRIC_INFERENCE_DEFAULT=openrouter
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-v1-...replace-with-your-key...
# OPENROUTER_GEN_MODEL=anthropic/claude-sonnet-4
# OPENROUTER_HTTP_REFERER=https://localhost
# OPENROUTER_APP_NAME=Fortemi-Workstation
# # Required — embeddings via Ollama:
# MATRIC_EMBEDDING_PROVIDER=ollama
# OLLAMA_BASE=http://ollama:11434
# OLLAMA_EMBED_MODEL=nomic-embed-text


# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Option 5 — llama.cpp server running on the host machine
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# You started llama-server yourself with something like:
#
#   llama-server --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8080 --model /path/to/model.gguf
#
# llama.cpp serves the OpenAI-compatible API at /v1/* paths. The Fortemi
# backend has a dedicated llamacpp provider that handles its quirks.
#
# Same Docker-to-host networking note as vLLM: use host.docker.internal
# (the compose file wires it for Linux too).
#
# llama.cpp can serve embeddings if started with --embedding, but the
# embedding model and the generation model must match. For embeddings,
# pairing with Ollama is simpler.
#
# MATRIC_INFERENCE_DEFAULT=llamacpp
# LLAMACPP_BASE_URL=http://host.docker.internal:8080
# # If you started llama-server with --api-key, set it here:
# # LLAMACPP_API_KEY=
# # Embeddings via Ollama (simpler than configuring llama.cpp embedding mode):
# MATRIC_EMBEDDING_PROVIDER=ollama
# OLLAMA_BASE=http://ollama:11434
# OLLAMA_EMBED_MODEL=nomic-embed-text
